## VII. DEFENSE MECHANISMS AND STANDARDIZATION ROADMAP

To rectify the lack of control-plane authentication without disrupting CXL.mem coherency protocols, we propose a comprehensive, four-layer defense architecture targeting CXL 5.0 Engineering Change Requests (ECRs).

**D1: Hardware-Anchored Ownership Registers (ECR-FM-SEC-03)**  
Each vPPB and DCD extent must be strictly backed by a hardware ownership register in the switch ASIC that records the authoritative FM's SPDM device identity. The switch thereby acts as a zero-trust enforcer, rejecting any commands attempting to mutate vPPB bindings or extent states unless the identity matches, effectively mitigating GAP-3 and GAP-4.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant FM as Legitimate FM
    participant Switch as CXL Switch (Hardware)
    participant Attacker as Unauthenticated Attacker

    Note over FM, Switch: 1. FM Registration (Secure Boot)
    FM->>Switch: CLAIM_OWNERSHIP (SPDM Certificate Thumbprint)
    Switch->>Switch: Hardware Ownership Register Locked to FM Identity

    Note over Attacker, Switch: 2. Attacker attempts ATK-1 (vPPB-Rebind) or ATK-3 (DCDrain)
    Attacker->>Switch: UNBIND_VPPB / DCD_RELEASE_CAPACITY 
    Switch->>Switch: Compare Sender MCTP Identity vs. Ownership Register
    Note over Switch: Mismatch! Sender is not the Legitimate FM (Closes GAP-3 & 4)
    Switch-->>Attacker: ERROR: Invalid Security State (Command Dropped)
```

**D2: Mandatory SPDM + RATS Session Binding (ECR-FM-SEC-02)**  
The CXL specification must boldly update the language in Section 7.6.3 [1, Sec. 7.6.3]. Instead of permissively allowing FM API commands to be transported as raw MCTP messages, the specification must mandate that FM API commands **shall** be transported as Secured Messages using SPDM over MCTP (DSP0276). Forcing all FM API commands to be encrypted and integrity-protected at the transport layer instantly neutralizes the Dolev-Yao network attacker.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Attacker as Network Attacker
    participant FM as Legitimate FM
    participant Switch as CXL Switch / Device

    Note over Switch: CXL 5.0 Spec mandates SPDM over MCTP (Section 7.6.3 "SHALL")
    
    Attacker->>Switch: Raw MCTP FM API Command (e.g., SET_PHY_PORT_STATE)
    Note over Switch: No SPDM session established
    Switch-->>Attacker: ERROR: Session Required / Command Dropped

    Note over FM, Switch: Legitimate FM Connection
    FM->>Switch: SPDM CHALLENGE_AUTH + RATS Attestation
    Switch->>Switch: Verify FM TEE firmware state & identity
    Switch-->>FM: SPDM Secure Session Established
    FM->>Switch: SPDM-Encrypted & Authenticated FM API Command
    Switch->>Switch: Decrypt, Authenticate, and Execute
    Switch-->>FM: SPDM-Encrypted Response
```

**D3: Orchestrator-Signed Command Tokens (ECR-FM-SEC-01)**  
FM API payloads must be updated to include a mandatory `CommandToken` field (an HMAC-SHA-256 keyed by the SPDM session) computed over the command opcode, payload, and sequence number. This directly patches GAP-1 and provides robust replay protection without altering the physical link layer.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant FM as Legitimate FM
    participant Switch as CXL Switch (Firmware)
    participant Attacker as Network Attacker

    Note over FM, Switch: Both entities share an SPDM-derived session key
    FM->>FM: Generate CommandToken<br/>(HMAC over opcode, payload, seq num)
    FM->>Switch: BIND_VPPB + CommandToken
    Switch->>Switch: Calculate expected HMAC & check sequence number
    Note over Switch: HMAC matches -> Execute Command
    Switch-->>FM: BIND_RESPONSE

    Note over Attacker, Switch: Attacker attempts command spoofing
    Attacker->>Switch: BIND_VPPB + Forged/Missing CommandToken
    Switch->>Switch: Calculate expected HMAC
    Note over Switch: HMAC mismatch! (Closes GAP-1)
    Switch-->>Attacker: ERROR: Invalid Token / Command Dropped
```

**D4: Per-Tenant Tunnel Attestation (ECR-FM-SEC-04)**  
CXL Tunnel Management Commands [1, Sec. 7.6.7.3.1] must be extended to include a mandatory `TunnelOriginToken` field. This carefully preserves legitimate tunneling functionality while forcing the outer switch to cryptographically verify the inner command's origin before forwarding it to the target device, successfully closing GAP-5.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Attacker as Tenant Attacker (Local Head)
    participant FM as Legitimate FM
    participant OuterSwitch as Outer CXL Switch
    participant InnerDevice as Target LD Pool CCI

    Note over FM, InnerDevice: Legitimate FM executing a tunneled command
    FM->>OuterSwitch: TUNNEL_MANAGEMENT_COMMAND + TunnelOriginToken
    OuterSwitch->>OuterSwitch: Cryptographically verify TunnelOriginToken against FM cert
    Note over OuterSwitch: Token Valid! Strip outer header
    OuterSwitch->>InnerDevice: Forward encapsulated inner command
    InnerDevice-->>OuterSwitch: Response
    OuterSwitch-->>FM: TUNNEL_RESPONSE

    Note over Attacker, InnerDevice: Attacker attempts ATK-4 (TunnelSpoof)
    Attacker->>OuterSwitch: TUNNEL_MANAGEMENT_COMMAND (No/Invalid Token)
    OuterSwitch->>OuterSwitch: Cryptographically verify TunnelOriginToken
    Note over OuterSwitch: Token Invalid or Missing! (Closes GAP-5)
    OuterSwitch-->>Attacker: ERROR: Unauthorized Tunnel Origin (Dropped)
```

